# Testing Rules

## Philosophy

All external dependencies (OpenRouter, PubMed, ClinicalTrials.gov, FDA, EMA) must be testable without live access.
Use mocked HTTP responses for unit tests.

## MVP 1 test categories

### Schemas
- RawInput validation and edge cases
- NormalizedINN, NormalizedDisease validation
- IntakeEnrichmentOutput completeness
- HumanDecision variants
- RunStatus transitions

### PDF handling
- SHA-256 hash computation
- New/unchanged/updated detection
- Text extraction produces correct chunks
- Missing file handling

### Intake enrichment agent
- Calls LLM with correct prompts
- Returns validated IntakeEnrichmentOutput
- Retries on validation failure
- Raises StructuredOutputError after retry exhaustion

### Structured LLM client
- Validates against Pydantic model
- Repair retry on validation failure
- Logs all attempts

### Orchestrator
- Full flow: create -> PDFs -> enrich -> verify -> approve -> complete
- Rejection flow
- Needs revision flow
- Failed enrichment flow
- Status transitions are valid

### Obsidian writer
- Run note creation and update
- Drug and disease entity notes
- Decision notes
- PDF source notes

### CLI
- Command parsing
- Input validation
- Human verification interaction

## MVP 2+ test categories

### Connectors (PubMed, ClinicalTrials, FDA, EMA)
- Correct query building
- Result parsing
- Zero results handling
- HTTP error handling
- Malformed response handling

### Scientific agent
- Requires human-approved input
- Validates structured output
- Handles partial connector failures

## Golden fixtures

Create fixtures for: known INN/disease pair, test PDFs, mock API responses, valid/invalid agent outputs.

## Coverage priority

Behavior coverage over line coverage. Critical paths: schema validation, evidence normalization, memo writing, failure handling.
